content: Finally back in NYC! The subway's familiar rumble is strangely comforting after the silence of Mount Fuji.
Just turned 22, and the city's energy feels like it's celebrating with me. Time to put some of those birthday wishes into action.
Met with a mentor for coffee. Discussed AI's potential in finance; he's intrigued by my $XVI lessons and wants to see my startup pitch.
Spent the day coding a prototype for my AI-driven trading bot. It's slow but showing promise. This could be my ticket in.
Joined an online forum for blockchain enthusiasts. Got some invaluable feedback on my quantum computing blockchain security ideas.
Started applying to tech-forward companies. It's nerve-wracking but exhilarating. Each application feels like a step closer to my dream job.
Had a virtual interview with a startup. They're impressed with my Python skills but want to see more blockchain experience.
Decided to enroll in an online course on quantum computing. This could be the edge I need.
Took a break from coding to reflect on past investments. Realized $XVI was more about the hype than the fundamentals. Learning to look beyond the noise.
Reached out to friends from Japan. Their insights on market trends are helping shape my recovery strategy. Perspective is everything.
Set up a meeting with a potential investor for my startup idea. They're interested in the AI integration aspect.
